[+1621] Daily Show Explores the Self-Dumbing Down of Fox & Friends
item.description: Jon Stewart last night took down Fox & Friends for using poll numbers on global warming -- more specifically, "climate gate" -- that added up to 120 percent. Then he zeroed in on host Gretchen Carlson for playing dumb -- even though she was valedictorian of her high school class, graduated with honors from Stanford and studied at Oxford.

item.title: [+1439] Outraged NYC Cyclists Re-Paint Bike Lane, Guerilla Style
item.description: 2 men were arrested yesterday for trying to re-paint a bike lane on a 14-block in Brooklyn. The bike lane was removed by the city because of complaints by local groups. The video (below) of the repainting concludes with this warning for the city: "Do not try to remove [bike lanes], or we will put them back for our own safety."

item.title: [+689] Stem Cells Can Be Engineered To Attack HIV
item.description: UCLA researchers this week published data that for the first time shows human blood stem cells can be engineered to attack HIV-infected cells and that the process could not only prove to be a breakthrough for AIDS patients but also for the sufferers of other viral diseases.

item.title: [+676] GOP Politician In S&M Scandal Fought To Ban Gay Sex
item.description: Rod Jetton, the former Missouri House Speaker, fired a state lawmaker from his committee chairmanship in 2007 because the lawmaker had changed a bill in order to end a state ban on gay sex -- or what Jetton called "deviate sexual intercourse." Jetton was charged with felony assault Monday after a girlfriend alleged that he had beaten and choked her

item.title: [+595] 15 Hacks Every Dropbox User Should Know
item.description: When you get right down to it, Dropbox is a pretty simple app. It syncs folders --that’s it. But what makes Dropbox amazing is the sheer number of different ways you can use that functionality, by itself or in conjunction with other programs, to improve your computing experience.

item.title: [+522] The Most Psychedelic Lake on Earth [W/ PICS]
item.description: The Spotted Lake near the city of Osoyoos in British Columbia, right at the Washington stateborder, is not the result of someone’s too vivid imagination but of the many different mineral deposits found in it: The lake is rich in calcium, sodium and magnesium sulphate (Epsom salts) and even silver and titanium.
